            <pb n="2" facs="#f0001"/>
            <div n="1">
                <head>
                    <hi rendition="#i">Extent and Population of America.</hi>
                </head>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <dateline>
                    <hi rendition="#k">London,</hi> Oct. 17</dateline>
                <p>&#x2014;The following es-<lb break="no"/>timate of the extent, in square
                        leagues,<lb break="yes"/>and population, of the continent of<lb break="yes"
                    />America in 1822, was lately transmitted<lb break="yes"/>by Baron de Humboldt
                    from Paris, to<lb break="yes"/>President Bolivar, with the accompany-<lb
                        break="no"/>ing letter:</p>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <table>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="#i">Sq. Leagues.</hi></cell>
                        <cell>
                            <hi rendition="#i">Population</hi></cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Mexico or New Spain</cell>
                        <cell>75830</cell>
                        <cell>6800000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Guatemala</cell>
                        <cell>16740</cell>
                        <cell>1600000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Cuba and Puerto-Rico</cell>
                        <cell> 4430</cell>
                        <cell>800000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell rows="3">Colombia <list rendition="#leftBraced">
                            <item>Venezuela</item>
                            <item>New Granada</item>
                        </list></cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>33700</cell>
                        <cell> 900000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>58250</cell>
                        <cell>1800000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row/>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Peru</cell>
                        <cell>42150</cell>
                        <cell>1400000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Chile</cell>
                        <cell>14240</cell>
                        <cell>1100000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Buenos Ayres</cell>
                        <cell>126770</cell>
                        <cell>2000000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell>_____________</cell>
                        <cell>_____________</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Total formerly Spanish</cell>
                        <cell>372110</cell>
                        <cell>16400000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell>United States</cell>
                        <cell>125440</cell>
                        <cell>10200000</cell>
                    </row>
                    <lb break="yes"/>
                    <row>
                        <cell>Brazil</cell>
                        <cell>256990</cell>
                        <cell> 4000000</cell>
                    </row>
                </table>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                
                
                <p>The above surfaces have been calcu-<lb break="no"/>lated with great care, on maps
                        rectified<lb break="yes"/>by astronomical observations. The<lb break="yes"
                    />calculations have been several times<lb break="yes"/>repeated by M. Mathieu
                    Member of the<lb break="yes"/>Board of Longitude and of the Institute,<lb
                        break="yes"/>as well as by myself. The results dif-<lb break="no"/>fer from
                    those published in <choice>
                        <sic>1819</sic>
                        <corr type="editorial">1809</corr>
                    </choice> in the<lb break="yes"/>political essay on Mexico. Then the<lb
                        break="yes"/>inhabited parts alone had been calcula-<lb break="no"/>ted,
                    without including the desert region<lb break="yes"/>over which the independent
                    tribes of<lb break="yes"/>the indigenous inhabitants wander.&#x2014;<lb
                        break="yes"/>Now the whole extent of each country,<lb break="yes"/>to its
                    furthest limits has been measured.</p>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <p>The population of the different parts<lb break="yes"/>of <choice>
                        <sic><hi rendition="#i">cidevant</hi></sic>
                        <corr type="editorial"><hi rendition="#i">ci-devant</hi></corr>
                    </choice> Spanish America is uncer-<lb break="no"/>tain, nevertheless each
                    portion has been<lb break="yes"/>calculated according to the latest <choice>
                        <sic>dates,</sic>
                        <corr type="editorial">data</corr>
                    </choice><lb break="yes"/>which have reached me. The present<lb break="yes"
                    />estimate ought to be considered in the<lb break="yes"/>same light as all my
                    other works on A-<lb break="no"/>merica; they are no other than essays, in<lb
                        break="yes"/>which every thing will have to be done<lb break="yes"/>over
                    again. Statistical calculations can<lb break="yes"/>only be rendered perfect by
                    degrees, in<lb break="yes"/>in like manner as the elements of mete-<lb
                        break="no"/>orological and astronomical tables.</p>
                <lb break="yes"/>
                <p>
                    <hi rendition="#i">Comparison.</hi>&#x2014;Spain contains 16,094<lb break="yes"
                    />square leagues&#x2014;Europe contains 304,-<lb break="no"/>710 square leagues,
                    and the whole of<lb break="yes"/>Southern America, 581,891 square<lb break="yes"
                    />leagues.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>
                        <hi rendition="#et">
                            <hi rendition="#k">Humboldt.</hi>
                        </hi>
                    </salute>
                </closer>
